    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-05-18T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-05-18T17:00:00-05:00" n="765"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d765">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 I’m Alone/2184: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Canada</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacNider</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-18T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 18, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>48. Consul General Frost has advised Department that he and Doris Corrigan, an
                    American citizen and visa clerk in Consulate General have been subpoenaed to
                    appear in court at Montreal on May 19th to produce official documents in their
                    custody and testify in habeas corpus proceedings involving Marvin J. Clark.</p>
                <p>Bring matter to attention Department of External Affairs pointing out that under
                    principles of international law official archives of consular offices are not
                    subject to subpoena requiring production in judicial proceedings and that
                    consular officers and their employees cannot properly be required to testify
                    concerning their official acts. State that Consul General Frost has accordingly
                    been instructed not to testify nor to permit Miss Corrigan to testify or produce
                    documents.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
